{"title": "Small, modular power plants in Singapore may be a reality soon but more research required", "tags": "opinion", "timestamp": "2023-04-25", "content": "The advent of newer and safer technologies in the nuclear industry will allow Singapore to meet its growing energy needs and carbon-neutral ambitions by 2050.\nAdvanced small modular reactors (SMRs) and floating nuclear power plants (FNPPs) are increasingly seen as potential \u201cgame changers\u201d for small, land-constrained countries."}